From: Henry Tieman <henry.w.tieman@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 2 Aug 2019 01:25:24 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 104/289] ice: fix adminq calls during remove

commit ae2bdbb45d38ee2ec67a958bf221138b58817c82 upstream.

The order of operations was incorrect in ice_remove(). The code would
try to use adminq operations after the adminq was disabled. This caused
all adminq calls to fail and possibly timeout waiting.

Signed-off-by: Henry Tieman <henry.w.tieman@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Tested-by: Andrew Bowers <andrewx.bowers@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Liwei Song <liwei.song@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c
index 3a963e93b28a..bbf3fc4ac0c5 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c
@@ -2634,9 +2634,9 @@ static void ice_remove(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 			continue;
 		ice_vsi_free_q_vectors(pf->vsi[i]);
 	}
-	ice_clear_interrupt_scheme(pf);
 	ice_deinit_pf(pf);
 	ice_deinit_hw(&pf->hw);
+	ice_clear_interrupt_scheme(pf);
 	pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
 }
 
